```

---

### 🟠 MEDIUM — No CORS Policy (OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration)

No CORS configuration means the default browser same-origin policy is in effect, but there's no explicit allowlist. This is fragile and may lead to overly permissive settings when CORS is eventually needed.

**Recommendation:** Set an explicit CORS policy:
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com'],  // Explicit allowlist, never '*' with credentials
  methods: ['GET'],
  credentials: false,
}));
```

---

### 🟠 MEDIUM — No Global Error Handler (OWASP A09: Security Logging & Monitoring Failures)

If an unhandled error occurs, Express's default error handler will send the full stack trace to the client in development mode, leaking internals.

**Recommendation:** Add an error-handling middleware at the end of the middleware chain:
```js
